review:
After too much of research on which doc to go for i finally expressed my concern with a neighbour amd she suggested Dr Kulkarni. The moment we visited her nursing home we were convinced this is the place we want to deliver our precious first baby. Our very basic criteria for selection of a gynac was that We dint want to visit a hospital with visiting docs as we strongly felt commercialisation has become the core of every hospital these days and only a doc who owned the nursing home would find it all in her heart to keep up to it. secndly we wanted to go for a senior exp gynac with min 15-20 yrs of exp and dr kulkarni was just the perfect one for us. My early pregnancy results showed very low baby heartbeat and the doc handheld my situation ever carefully since the first day until today. As i enter my secnd trimester i am cnvinced the doc will cntinue to do the same. The hospital hygiene and staff are too just as humble and involved as the doc herself.
Looking forward to my normal delivery under doc supervision.
reply_text: Thank you very much for your kind words.We look forward to continue serving you and your family. Kulkarni Hospital

review:
I got an appointment with Ma‚Äôam for surgical abortion through Prystncare. She is actually very good at her work! I was 14 weeks pregnant on the day of abortion- scared a bit from procedure plus from needles. She understood that I am afraid of needles inside OT within a second and diverted my mind by asking me my name and with comments. I didn‚Äôt even realised when the procedure was completed, I got complete care by the people there at hospital- they were very humble with me. I got discharged by night. **** *** **** ********* ********* **** **** ********** I didn‚Äôt had much issues just a bit of cramping for the last 4-5 days, but that‚Äôs pretty normal as we all do experience the same during periods. 

I would surely recommend her for treatments! I don‚Äôt have an experience about deliveries and all but by this experience I could say the hospital is trustworthy and you can completely rely on them for the treatment!

reply_text:
Dear Patient, at 4.1% of all deliveries (including electives), you are at least 5 TIMES LESS LIKELY to have a C-section here than at most other hospitals in Mumbai. We understand that childbirth is definitely one of the most momentous and celebrated occasions in a woman‚Äôs life and can often be stressful. 
However, when the patient is 37+ years of age and after having tried for several hours (over 6 hours based on our records) at some point the doctor has to take a call for patients safety. Your husbands consent for the same is on our records. Also note that we've had the 4.1% C-section record over the last 29 years of practice with several thousand safe and sound deliveries. While we regret that you had a poor experience with us, please try and understand that we did what we did in your best interest. We hope you and your healthy baby girl have a wonderful life ahead.
